  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7037.76 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 and the massive +12B gamma wall at 7050, dealers are currently in a neutral hedging stance but poised to sell any push toward 7050. The PIN regime with 117B in total GEX creates a strong mean-reverting environment, with dealers acting as stabilizers—they'll aggressively sell the 7050-7100 gamma wall cluster and buy any dip toward 7000-7015. Key levels: watch for dealer selling pressure into 7050+ and buying support if we test back toward the 7000/7015 zone.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect range-bound action between 7000-7050 with resistance at the upper end.",
